WEBVTT

00:00:39.556 --> 00:00:41.915
Single people's blind dates usually go on

00:00:41.915 --> 00:00:45.111
for around two and a half hours
on a weekend afternoon.

00:00:57.157 --> 00:00:59.143
The right amount of space between two strangers

00:00:59.143 --> 00:01:01.355
on a first meeting is 45 centimeters.

00:01:01.355 --> 00:01:03.990
Too close and it gets awkward.

00:01:03.990 --> 00:01:07.675
Too far and the spark fades.

00:01:08.293 --> 00:01:10.462
Falling for someone doesn't take

00:01:10.462 --> 00:01:12.564
five minutes or even one.

00:01:12.564 --> 00:01:13.882
It only takes five seconds.

00:01:13.882 --> 00:01:16.403
According to experts, those five seconds are

00:01:16.403 --> 00:01:18.220
all it takes to make up your mind.

00:01:18.220 --> 00:01:20.856
Everything about my blind date was on track,

00:01:20.856 --> 00:01:23.350
safely moving along,

00:01:23.350 --> 00:01:26.311
right up until he said this.

00:01:26.311 --> 00:01:28.271
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:01:28.271 --> 00:01:32.692
Are you open to dating

00:01:32.692 --> 00:01:34.619
with marriage in mind?

00:01:37.531 --> 00:01:39.408
Did you just say marriage?

00:01:39.408 --> 00:01:40.951
Yes.

00:01:40.951 --> 00:01:43.211
I want to get married.

00:01:46.415 --> 00:01:48.166
I'm not getting any younger,

00:01:48.166 --> 00:01:50.002
and I'd really like to see
where this goes with you...

00:01:50.002 --> 00:01:50.794
Oh, it's cold!

00:01:50.794 --> 00:01:52.470
My goodness.

00:01:56.104 --> 00:01:57.106
Oh no!

00:01:57.106 --> 00:01:59.302
My goodness.

00:01:59.302 --> 00:02:00.345
Here, use this.

00:02:00.345 --> 00:02:02.313
Thank you.

00:02:03.564 --> 00:02:05.726
Oh no.

00:02:05.726 --> 00:02:07.439
Are you okay?

00:02:07.439 --> 00:02:09.689
I'm so sorry.

00:02:09.689 --> 00:02:11.614
I'm screwed.

00:02:12.439 --> 00:02:15.701
Who told me to wear
a bright outfit to a blind date?

00:02:21.272 --> 00:02:22.856
Marriage?

00:02:22.856 --> 00:02:24.939
It's barely been thirty minutes.

00:02:24.939 --> 00:02:27.421
How could anyone say yes to that?

00:02:45.564 --> 00:02:49.230
I rubbed it with everything I had,
but the stain won't budge.

00:02:49.230 --> 00:02:51.522
Scrubbing too hard can ruin the fibers.

00:02:51.522 --> 00:02:54.856
You might end up
with a stain that never comes out.

00:02:54.856 --> 00:02:56.735
Are you serious?

00:02:56.735 --> 00:02:59.105
I really love this outfit.

00:02:59.105 --> 00:03:01.359
Gosh.

00:03:02.397 --> 00:03:04.147
Once you're home,

00:03:04.147 --> 00:03:06.410
let it sit in salt water first,
then sugar water,

00:03:06.410 --> 00:03:08.147
and toss it in the wash.

00:03:08.147 --> 00:03:10.791
Since soy sauce dissolves in water,
there's a good chance the stain will lift.

00:03:10.791 --> 00:03:12.717
Got it.

00:03:13.522 --> 00:03:15.712
It might be best to call it a night.

00:03:15.712 --> 00:03:17.847
Yeah.

00:03:25.597 --> 00:03:27.981
I feel terrible about today.

00:03:27.981 --> 00:03:29.939
You barely got to eat anything, right?

00:03:29.939 --> 00:03:31.897
There's always next time for a meal.

00:03:31.897 --> 00:03:33.230
Next time?

00:03:33.230 --> 00:03:35.731
My car's by the station. I'll drive you home.

00:03:35.731 --> 00:03:36.897
We can talk on the way...

00:03:36.897 --> 00:03:37.734
No, it's fine.

00:03:37.734 --> 00:03:39.439
I'll get home on my own.

00:03:39.439 --> 00:03:42.747
I don't want to trouble you
any more than I already have.

00:03:45.230 --> 00:03:47.105
All right.

00:03:47.105 --> 00:03:49.086
Take care getting home.

00:04:07.647 --> 00:04:09.224
How's the date going?

00:04:09.224 --> 00:04:11.977
You should be heading to a second spot by now.

00:04:11.977 --> 00:04:13.979
Your timing is unreal, as always.

00:04:13.979 --> 00:04:16.022
I'm on my way home.

00:04:16.022 --> 00:04:18.105
You read my text since the 1 is gone.

00:04:18.105 --> 00:04:19.192
Pay attention to your date.

00:04:19.192 --> 00:04:23.162
If you're into him, send me the sun emoji.

00:04:37.564 --> 00:04:39.553
That's him.

00:04:44.397 --> 00:04:47.772
[Episode 2]

00:04:47.772 --> 00:04:50.188
Your first setup,
and a guy shows up in a foreign car.

00:04:50.188 --> 00:04:51.147
Was it this one?

00:04:51.147 --> 00:04:53.023
What?

00:04:53.023 --> 00:04:55.355
I don't think this was it.

00:04:55.355 --> 00:04:57.647
How should I say this...

00:04:57.647 --> 00:04:59.524
It was white,

00:04:59.524 --> 00:05:00.942
kind of looked like a dolphin.

00:05:00.942 --> 00:05:03.236
- A dolphin?
- Yeah.

00:05:03.236 --> 00:05:05.329
Wait...

00:05:06.760 --> 00:05:09.660
This car?
A brand new one costs over 100 million won.

00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:11.238
Over a hundred million?

00:05:11.897 --> 00:05:15.423
It looks a little like it,

00:05:16.064 --> 00:05:18.884
but also completely off...

00:05:20.272 --> 00:05:22.680
What was it?

00:05:23.439 --> 00:05:25.683
You're sure it wasn't an SUV, right?

00:05:26.360 --> 00:05:27.700
Yeah.

00:05:27.700 --> 00:05:29.341
Isn't an SUV one of those big ones?

00:05:29.341 --> 00:05:31.439
With four wheels?

00:05:31.439 --> 00:05:34.191
All cars have four wheels, are you kidding me?

00:05:35.566 --> 00:05:39.147
Look, next time you meet him,
just snap a photo.

00:05:39.147 --> 00:05:40.953
That never crossed my mind.

00:05:40.953 --> 00:05:44.553
Why not just have him bring
proof of income while you're at it?

00:05:44.553 --> 00:05:45.654
I wonder

00:05:45.654 --> 00:05:47.238
if that guy in the fancy car

00:05:47.238 --> 00:05:50.075
was sizing you up by your bag that day.

00:05:50.075 --> 00:05:52.934
That's pretty cold coming from a mom.

00:05:52.934 --> 00:05:54.154
That's not what I meant.

00:05:54.154 --> 00:05:57.188
This is just, like, curiosity?

00:05:57.188 --> 00:05:59.439
Once you sit across
from someone at a blind date,

00:05:59.439 --> 00:06:02.470
you better be prepared to get sized up too.

00:06:03.213 --> 00:06:05.590
If you're meeting someone anyway,

00:06:05.590 --> 00:06:07.592
wouldn't a guy with a nice car
be the better pick?

00:06:07.592 --> 00:06:09.897
A luxury car can't be trash,

00:06:09.897 --> 00:06:12.222
so the guy driving it
can't be trash either, can he?

00:06:12.222 --> 00:06:12.912
Right.

00:06:12.912 --> 00:06:15.016
His family could've been rich for generations,

00:06:15.016 --> 00:06:17.147
or maybe he built it all himself
while still young.

00:06:17.147 --> 00:06:18.939
Or he could be car-poor.

00:06:18.939 --> 00:06:20.780
Car-poor?

00:06:28.321 --> 00:06:29.351
No,

00:06:29.351 --> 00:06:32.367
he didn't come off as the flashy type.

00:06:32.367 --> 00:06:34.588
You nagged me for years about not dating,

00:06:34.588 --> 00:06:36.147
and now you can't wait to hold me back?

00:06:36.147 --> 00:06:37.188
What?

00:06:37.188 --> 00:06:38.164
When did I do that?

00:06:38.164 --> 00:06:39.416
You pay for that yourself?

00:06:39.416 --> 00:06:43.211
Also, a guy who jumps straight
to marriage talk on date one

00:06:43.211 --> 00:06:45.213
is just weird, no?

00:06:45.213 --> 00:06:47.023
Start doing family visits

00:06:47.023 --> 00:06:50.667
and wedding invites now,
the thrill will be dead in a year.

00:06:50.667 --> 00:06:52.446
What a fun time dating that'll be.

00:06:52.446 --> 00:06:54.848
Oh please, let's not jinx it...

00:06:54.848 --> 00:06:58.025
- Knock on wood.
- Knock on wood.

00:07:01.396 --> 00:07:05.064
So when's the next date?

00:07:05.064 --> 00:07:07.944
No clue, I haven't heard from him.

00:07:07.944 --> 00:07:10.522
No follow-up text yet?

00:07:10.522 --> 00:07:12.122
No.

00:07:12.857 --> 00:07:16.126
So he still hasn't gotten back to you.

00:07:16.870 --> 00:07:18.772
Whatever you do, don't text him first.

00:07:18.772 --> 00:07:20.965
You'll look way too eager.

00:07:24.252 --> 00:07:25.606
Aren't you leaving?

00:07:25.606 --> 00:07:26.685
It's late.

00:07:26.685 --> 00:07:29.139
Quit snacking on that stuff.

00:07:30.717 --> 00:07:33.561
He hasn't even texted,
so why are you searching that?

00:07:39.647 --> 00:07:43.362
Does the follow-up come with a deadline?

00:07:52.006 --> 00:07:54.564
[Average wait time for a date follow-up]

00:07:54.564 --> 00:07:57.293
Follow-up after a blind date...

00:07:58.870 --> 00:08:00.246
[How long before a follow-up usually comes?]

00:08:00.246 --> 00:08:01.581
[Weekend date, how soon is the follow-up?]

00:08:01.581 --> 00:08:02.665
[That same day]
[A day or two, tops?]

00:08:02.665 --> 00:08:03.500
[If the vibe's great,
plans are set on the spot]

00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:04.459
[Most people lock it in before leaving, no?]

00:08:04.459 --> 00:08:05.919
[Same day here too!]
[By the next day at most, right?]

00:08:05.919 --> 00:08:06.753
[It's usually just a few hours, isn't it?]

00:08:06.753 --> 00:08:07.796
[Before you even walk away!]

00:08:07.796 --> 00:08:08.713
[Definitely same day]

00:08:08.713 --> 00:08:09.585
[When the chemistry's there, it's instant]

00:08:24.012 --> 00:08:25.696
Excuse me.

00:08:29.439 --> 00:08:31.372
I didn't realize it was you.

00:08:31.372 --> 00:08:33.792
Did you get a new car?

00:08:33.792 --> 00:08:35.073
Oh, it's a company car.

00:08:35.073 --> 00:08:36.573
I always use the company vehicle, remember?

00:08:36.573 --> 00:08:38.052
What time did you get here?

00:08:38.052 --> 00:08:40.731
It's the weekend.
Please tell me you didn't pull an all-nighter.

00:08:40.731 --> 00:08:42.121
I got here once the sun was up.

00:08:42.121 --> 00:08:43.915
Didn't you say the trees already came in?

00:08:43.915 --> 00:08:46.471
They arrived,

00:08:46.471 --> 00:08:49.212
but the display still needs to be done.

00:08:49.212 --> 00:08:51.731
You showed up early
just to make me work, didn't you?

00:08:51.731 --> 00:08:53.933
Let me pitch in as well.

00:09:11.245 --> 00:09:13.111
The vibe is great.

00:09:13.111 --> 00:09:14.586
Mind if I take this?

00:09:14.586 --> 00:09:16.656
Go ahead, consider it your wages for the day

00:09:16.656 --> 00:09:18.939
and mark whatever catches your eye.

00:09:18.939 --> 00:09:20.105
Sure.

00:09:20.105 --> 00:09:21.160
You're eating before you leave, right?

00:09:21.160 --> 00:09:22.814
No, there's a place I need to stop by.

00:09:22.814 --> 00:09:25.756
Would it be okay if I showered here?

00:09:35.981 --> 00:09:37.662
Over here.

00:09:40.221 --> 00:09:41.543
What's wrong?

00:09:41.543 --> 00:09:44.434
- It's Sua's first time as a flower girl today.
- Yeah.

00:09:44.434 --> 00:09:46.188
I checked out what little kids
usually wear to weddings

00:09:46.188 --> 00:09:49.105
and chose something nice,
but she turned it down.

00:09:49.105 --> 00:09:52.150
The more you try to make it
not look like "dad-picked" clothes,

00:09:52.150 --> 00:09:53.860
the more tacky they actually get.

00:09:53.860 --> 00:09:56.924
I handled all your outfits
even when your mom was around.

00:09:56.924 --> 00:09:59.384
Your mom's taste was never better than mine.

00:09:59.384 --> 00:10:00.783
Come on.

00:10:00.783 --> 00:10:02.504
Sua, you're going to hurt your dad's feelings.

00:10:02.504 --> 00:10:05.304
And honestly, I think you look great in that.

00:10:05.304 --> 00:10:08.147
That's because I can pull off anything.

00:10:08.147 --> 00:10:10.990
Seriously, you can't do any better than that?

00:10:11.907 --> 00:10:13.689
Fix your buttons,

00:10:13.689 --> 00:10:15.723
and sweep your hair to the side.

00:10:16.480 --> 00:10:18.308
Step over here.

00:10:22.694 --> 00:10:23.327
Hey!

00:10:23.327 --> 00:10:25.023
All set.

00:10:25.023 --> 00:10:26.567
Let's go.

00:10:37.772 --> 00:10:39.117
- You made it?
- Yeah.

00:10:39.117 --> 00:10:40.615
Look over here, please.

00:10:40.615 --> 00:10:43.160
One, two, three!

00:10:43.160 --> 00:10:44.827
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

00:10:44.827 --> 00:10:45.870
Come here, hurry up.

00:10:45.870 --> 00:10:47.188
- No, I'm good.
- Why not?

00:10:47.188 --> 00:10:49.749
It's pretty crowded in here,
so we'll hang out there.

00:10:49.749 --> 00:10:51.011
- Thank you.
- Congratulations.

00:10:51.011 --> 00:10:52.835
Thank you.

00:10:52.835 --> 00:10:55.023
Fourteen years of dating

00:10:55.023 --> 00:10:56.397
and they finally tied the knot.

00:10:56.397 --> 00:10:57.303
I know.

00:10:57.303 --> 00:10:58.284
Oh, and get this.

00:10:58.284 --> 00:11:00.689
Pretty sure they split up around ten times.

00:11:00.689 --> 00:11:03.731
Oh look, our graduation picture.

00:11:03.731 --> 00:11:05.455
Hyun Ju's in this one too.

00:11:05.455 --> 00:11:07.376
She looked so pure and wide-eyed back then.

00:11:07.376 --> 00:11:09.522
Nobody would've guessed
she'd cut you loose that coldly

00:11:09.522 --> 00:11:11.439
six years down the road.

00:11:11.439 --> 00:11:13.148
Hey, you paying attention?

00:11:13.148 --> 00:11:14.955
Not interested?

00:11:14.955 --> 00:11:17.284
- Make sure you grab that bouquet.
- See you in a bit.

00:11:19.939 --> 00:11:21.823
Oh, you're looking.

00:11:21.823 --> 00:11:22.908
Have they lost their mind?

00:11:22.908 --> 00:11:26.001
A heads-up about Hyun Ju showing up
would've been nice.

00:11:27.981 --> 00:11:30.714
Why don't they just seat you guys
at the same table?

00:11:33.626 --> 00:11:34.649
Hello, everyone.

00:11:34.649 --> 00:11:37.749
I'll be hosting today's ceremony,
and I'm the groom's...

00:11:37.749 --> 00:11:39.748
Wonderful seating plan they came up with.

00:11:39.748 --> 00:11:41.868
Relationships end,
but classmates stay classmates.

00:11:41.868 --> 00:11:43.109
By the way,

00:11:43.109 --> 00:11:45.023
word is you're tying the knot this year?

00:11:45.023 --> 00:11:46.809
Going for the bouquet today too?

00:11:46.809 --> 00:11:47.557
Yes.

00:11:47.557 --> 00:11:48.641
I already called dibs on it.

00:11:48.641 --> 00:11:50.488
I want to make it happen
by the end of the year.

00:11:50.488 --> 00:11:51.649
That's great.

00:11:51.649 --> 00:11:52.603
Hey.

00:11:52.603 --> 00:11:54.397
Did you hear that the chair he designed

00:11:54.397 --> 00:11:57.312
went for thirteen million won at an art fair?

00:11:57.312 --> 00:11:59.023
- Oh, really?
- Seriously?

00:11:59.023 --> 00:12:02.363
Honestly, the first couple of years
running the business were rough.

00:12:02.363 --> 00:12:04.293
Zero projects, zero income.

00:12:04.293 --> 00:12:07.118
All he could rely on
were the people around him,

00:12:07.118 --> 00:12:09.564
and that's exactly when someone left.

00:12:09.564 --> 00:12:10.472
Lee Eun Ho.

00:12:10.472 --> 00:12:13.791
Loneliness doesn't check your schedule first.

00:12:13.791 --> 00:12:16.378
Eun Ho, your wife's never felt lonely
because of you?

00:12:16.378 --> 00:12:17.230
Hey.

00:12:17.230 --> 00:12:19.814
- Please welcome Sua.
- Don't cross the line.

00:12:19.814 --> 00:12:20.939
You started it first. Drop it.

00:12:20.939 --> 00:12:22.293
Our adorable flower girl, Sua...

00:12:22.293 --> 00:12:23.510
Did I?

00:12:23.510 --> 00:12:25.368
is now entering.

00:12:26.971 --> 00:12:30.147
Sua, look over here, look here.

00:12:30.147 --> 00:12:32.605
Sua, that's it.

00:12:32.605 --> 00:12:33.721
She's so pretty.

00:12:33.721 --> 00:12:35.153
Sua,

00:12:35.153 --> 00:12:36.522
look over here for a second.

00:12:36.522 --> 00:12:38.355
Oh my, whose daughter is she?

00:12:38.355 --> 00:12:40.659
So cute.

00:12:43.113 --> 00:12:44.958
Song Tae Seop.

00:12:49.147 --> 00:12:51.795
How come you stayed silent that entire time?

00:12:55.522 --> 00:12:56.665
It's been a long time.

00:12:56.665 --> 00:12:57.731
Yeah, it has.

00:12:57.731 --> 00:12:59.671
You got dumped after dating someone that long.

00:12:59.671 --> 00:13:00.672
The least you could've done was say,
"Come back."

00:13:00.672 --> 00:13:01.595
"Be well."

00:13:01.595 --> 00:13:03.070
Or even, "I hope you're miserable."

00:13:03.070 --> 00:13:06.314
Any one of those three
would've been the decent thing to do.

00:13:06.314 --> 00:13:07.831
I wasn't grown up enough

00:13:07.831 --> 00:13:10.550
to let go of someone I loved with any grace.

00:13:10.550 --> 00:13:14.318
I wanted to reject everything,
but I swallowed it and threw myself into work.

00:13:15.314 --> 00:13:17.613
The years just flew by.

00:13:19.439 --> 00:13:21.814
So...

00:13:21.814 --> 00:13:23.105
life's been good?

00:13:23.105 --> 00:13:25.621
One, two, three.

00:13:26.522 --> 00:13:28.082
Yeah.

00:13:28.082 --> 00:13:29.272
I thought maybe you'd lost everything

00:13:29.272 --> 00:13:32.252
and ended up crawling back
to the family business.

00:13:32.897 --> 00:13:36.062
Part of me always wanted
to run into you one more time.

00:13:36.062 --> 00:13:38.086
And congrats on the wedding.

00:13:38.086 --> 00:13:39.123
What about you?

00:13:39.123 --> 00:13:40.462
No one in your life?

00:13:40.462 --> 00:13:42.338
I haven't heard a single thing.

00:13:42.338 --> 00:13:45.755
Any girl who dates you is in for a headache.
You can't handle two things at once.

00:13:48.147 --> 00:13:49.895
Actually...

00:14:01.377 --> 00:14:03.283
I had a blind date.

00:14:08.839 --> 00:14:10.480
Let's go.

00:14:10.480 --> 00:14:11.993
What?

00:14:11.993 --> 00:14:12.981
Isn't that Hyun Ju's bouquet?

00:14:12.981 --> 00:14:15.439
- I've done my part celebrating.
- Song Tae Seop. Lee Eun Ho.

00:14:15.439 --> 00:14:17.832
Run. Let's go!

00:14:17.832 --> 00:14:22.314
[68 hours since the blind date]

00:14:28.427 --> 00:14:31.314
Yu Been, Woo Hyuk, I need those product photos

00:14:31.314 --> 00:14:32.722
for the design award entries to look top-notch.

00:14:32.722 --> 00:14:33.307
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:14:33.307 --> 00:14:35.787
You mentioned you're heading to Jeju
for the pitch in person, right?

00:14:35.787 --> 00:14:38.248
The roastery owner is counting on it.

00:14:38.248 --> 00:14:40.314
There are technical details
I should walk them through face to face,

00:14:40.314 --> 00:14:42.228
- so I'll leave tomorrow night.
- Okay.

00:14:42.228 --> 00:14:43.232
Take Jin Su with you.

00:14:43.232 --> 00:14:45.127
I'll book the flights and hotel.

00:14:45.127 --> 00:14:46.527
Next, the select shop.

00:14:46.527 --> 00:14:47.188
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:14:47.188 --> 00:14:48.088
Demo on Monday.

00:14:48.088 --> 00:14:49.428
Confirmed for Thursday.

00:14:49.428 --> 00:14:50.281
Alright.

00:14:50.281 --> 00:14:51.992
That's it for today.

00:14:58.766 --> 00:14:59.814
Come here.

00:14:59.814 --> 00:15:01.550
What?

00:15:02.731 --> 00:15:06.355
So when do I get the blind date details?

00:15:06.355 --> 00:15:08.598
Is she pretty?

00:15:11.689 --> 00:15:14.514
That's adorable.

00:15:14.514 --> 00:15:16.148
Such a baby.

00:15:18.768 --> 00:15:19.810
She looks just like her.

00:15:19.810 --> 00:15:22.022
You're obsessed with her!

00:15:22.022 --> 00:15:24.564
So, is she pretty?

00:15:24.564 --> 00:15:26.908
Like, is she your type?

00:15:28.277 --> 00:15:30.426
Yeah, I guess.

00:15:30.426 --> 00:15:34.564
Am I finally going to see you date again?

00:15:34.564 --> 00:15:37.856
Please tell me you bought her a good meal
and gave her a ride home.

00:15:37.856 --> 00:15:40.415
Oh, well...

00:15:40.415 --> 00:15:42.083
That doesn't sound good.

00:15:42.083 --> 00:15:43.292
Did you set up a second date?

00:15:43.292 --> 00:15:46.926
It's just that this week is slammed,
so I figured maybe next week?

00:15:46.926 --> 00:15:49.707
Even if you're meeting later,
you should ask her out now.

00:15:49.707 --> 00:15:50.387
Pull out your phone.

00:15:50.387 --> 00:15:51.897
No, just give it to me. I'll do it my...

00:15:51.897 --> 00:15:54.019
I'll take care of it when I get off.

00:15:54.814 --> 00:15:56.426
Then leave. Now.

00:15:56.426 --> 00:15:57.557
Get out of here. Go!

00:15:57.557 --> 00:15:59.399
What's the holdup?

00:16:15.482 --> 00:16:18.043
I'm home.

00:16:35.647 --> 00:16:38.897
If you live alone,
you have to take better care of yourself.

00:17:12.814 --> 00:17:14.850
What's wrong with my back?

00:17:17.355 --> 00:17:19.646
My phone...

00:17:46.916 --> 00:17:50.545
[90 hours since the blind date]

00:18:03.974 --> 00:18:06.985
[Meeting for New Summer Bingsu Menu]

00:18:08.439 --> 00:18:10.405
Still nothing.

00:18:14.568 --> 00:18:17.803
What's going on with Ui Yeong today?
She's been out of it all day.

00:18:18.605 --> 00:18:21.500
Maybe something went down on that blind date.

00:18:22.147 --> 00:18:24.323
Wait, she had a blind date?

00:18:24.323 --> 00:18:27.105
She always pretends
she doesn't care about that stuff.

00:18:27.105 --> 00:18:29.341
Did I say it was a blind date?

00:18:42.023 --> 00:18:44.890
So summer bingsu is
where the hotel's reputation is on the line?

00:18:44.890 --> 00:18:45.808
Exactly.

00:18:45.808 --> 00:18:48.064
We're aiming for fine dining standards.

00:18:48.064 --> 00:18:50.244
Only the finest melons.

00:18:50.244 --> 00:18:52.969
That's why I set up a blind tasting.

00:18:52.969 --> 00:18:54.876
- Really?
- For real?

00:19:01.939 --> 00:19:03.576
It just melts in my mouth.

00:19:03.576 --> 00:19:04.618
It's sweet.

00:19:04.618 --> 00:19:08.316
[Melon tasting scorecard]

00:19:13.480 --> 00:19:15.345
Isn't this good?

00:19:17.548 --> 00:19:18.564
This one's sweeter.

00:19:18.564 --> 00:19:21.017
Yeah, definitely.

00:19:22.052 --> 00:19:23.929
The scent on this one stands out more, though.

00:19:23.929 --> 00:19:25.473
[Honeydew]

00:19:25.473 --> 00:19:27.073
[Cantaloupe] [White Dream]

00:19:27.809 --> 00:19:29.005
[Haniwon] [Noeul] [Musk]

00:19:29.005 --> 00:19:32.521
The Musk tastes and smells wonderful,
but there's nothing exclusive about it.

00:19:32.521 --> 00:19:35.272
The Noeul is lighter on fragrance,

00:19:35.272 --> 00:19:38.027
but it brings a pumpkin-like flavor
with a cozy sweetness.

00:19:38.027 --> 00:19:40.905
The Haniwon checks a lot of boxes,
but the timing's off for the season.

00:19:40.905 --> 00:19:44.023
The White Dream is sweet enough,

00:19:44.023 --> 00:19:47.188
but it falls a little short on that crisp bite.

00:19:47.188 --> 00:19:50.345
For all-around balance,
the Cantaloupe takes it.

00:19:50.345 --> 00:19:52.208
Purchasing team,
track down a melon vendor for us.

00:19:52.208 --> 00:19:52.985
Yes.

00:19:52.985 --> 00:19:55.211
Once the melons arrive,
let's start recipe testing right away.

00:19:55.211 --> 00:19:56.565
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:19:56.565 --> 00:19:58.272
I can't wait.

00:19:58.272 --> 00:20:00.056
Me too.

00:20:02.316 --> 00:20:06.647
He's been ignoring his phone the whole day.
Did he step out for food?

00:20:06.647 --> 00:20:07.807
Hey, Bo Yoon, Joon Hyung.

00:20:07.807 --> 00:20:08.432
- Yeah?
- Yeah?

00:20:08.432 --> 00:20:09.756
Where's Tae Seop?

00:20:09.756 --> 00:20:11.737
He didn't have lunch with us.

00:20:11.737 --> 00:20:14.416
Come to think of it,
has anyone even seen him today?

00:20:14.416 --> 00:20:16.564
Is he a no-show today?

00:20:16.564 --> 00:20:17.757
Tae Seop?

00:20:17.757 --> 00:20:20.236
He never missed a single day
from grade school through college.

00:20:20.236 --> 00:20:22.537
He'd only catch a cold when classes were out.

00:20:32.438 --> 00:20:34.841
Hey, you in there or not?

00:20:35.522 --> 00:20:37.397
Eun Ho.

00:20:37.397 --> 00:20:39.314
Hey.

00:20:39.314 --> 00:20:41.218
Wait, you're inside?

00:20:41.218 --> 00:20:43.099
Hey! Open the door!

00:20:43.099 --> 00:20:43.968
I can't.

00:20:43.968 --> 00:20:46.147
You have to come in yourself.

00:20:46.147 --> 00:20:47.814
The passcode is

00:20:47.814 --> 00:20:49.016
2621.

00:20:49.016 --> 00:20:50.683
2, 1?

00:20:50.683 --> 00:20:51.814
2621.

00:20:51.814 --> 00:20:53.064
What?

00:20:53.064 --> 00:20:55.271
2616?

00:20:55.271 --> 00:20:57.441
2621, you idiot.

00:20:59.946 --> 00:21:00.981
Hey.

00:21:00.981 --> 00:21:02.147
Yeah.

00:21:02.147 --> 00:21:03.988
Tae Seop!

00:21:03.988 --> 00:21:05.030
Song Tae Seop!

00:21:05.030 --> 00:21:07.241
Don't touch me.

00:21:07.241 --> 00:21:08.701
Hey!

00:21:08.701 --> 00:21:12.663
I answered you. What's with the water?

00:21:12.663 --> 00:21:13.664
What's wrong with you?

00:21:13.664 --> 00:21:14.873
Don't touch me.

00:21:14.873 --> 00:21:16.188
Help me up.

00:21:16.188 --> 00:21:19.260
- Let's go to the hospital.
- Help me up. Slowly.

00:21:22.674 --> 00:21:24.599
Is it a big deal?

00:21:29.473 --> 00:21:31.606
The thing is...

00:21:32.641 --> 00:21:33.875
It's a muscle knot.

00:21:33.875 --> 00:21:34.775
Sorry?

00:21:34.775 --> 00:21:36.314
A muscle knot?

00:21:36.314 --> 00:21:39.235
But he's completely immobilized?

00:21:39.235 --> 00:21:41.636
He was lying there like that
for a whole day straight.

00:21:41.636 --> 00:21:43.861
Traditional Korean medicine has this saying.

00:21:43.861 --> 00:21:45.395
"Nine out of ten."

00:21:45.395 --> 00:21:46.780
When someone has ten illnesses,

00:21:46.780 --> 00:21:49.867
nine of those come from blocked energy flow.

00:21:49.867 --> 00:21:51.296
Don't take it lightly.

00:21:51.296 --> 00:21:53.044
Get some acupuncture before you go.

00:21:53.647 --> 00:21:55.395
I can tell you're living by yourself.

00:21:55.395 --> 00:21:57.115
Yeah...

00:21:57.115 --> 00:21:59.665
Grown-ups need someone watching over them too.

00:21:59.665 --> 00:22:02.798
Save a friend as your emergency contact

00:22:02.798 --> 00:22:05.640
and share your door code with them.

00:22:06.843 --> 00:22:09.522
Being alone turns into

00:22:09.522 --> 00:22:11.771
dying alone.

00:22:17.314 --> 00:22:18.486
You've lost so much weight.

00:22:18.486 --> 00:22:19.766
Are you even up for the business trip?

00:22:19.766 --> 00:22:21.105
Want me to just send Jin Su instead?

00:22:21.105 --> 00:22:22.465
I'm definitely going.

00:22:22.465 --> 00:22:25.230
The acupuncture actually helped a lot.

00:22:25.230 --> 00:22:27.996
Being alone turns into dying alone.

00:22:32.147 --> 00:22:33.522
Gosh.

00:22:33.522 --> 00:22:35.420
Excuse me.

00:22:47.092 --> 00:22:50.355
I love that it's just us girls tonight.

00:22:50.355 --> 00:22:52.387
Come on. Tell me.

00:22:52.387 --> 00:22:54.147
Nobody has any drama?

00:22:54.147 --> 00:22:55.350
Oh, right.

00:22:55.350 --> 00:22:56.642
Hey.

00:22:56.642 --> 00:23:00.482
Word is Attorney Kang Do Hyun
has been hitting on you.

00:23:00.482 --> 00:23:03.565
Keep that up
and romance will overtake your workload.

00:23:03.565 --> 00:23:04.564
What?

00:23:04.564 --> 00:23:07.223
Dating is the last thing on my mind.

00:23:07.223 --> 00:23:08.238
How come?

00:23:08.238 --> 00:23:09.742
Give him a chance.

00:23:09.742 --> 00:23:12.290
See what happens

00:23:13.285 --> 00:23:15.662
when you shut everyone out?

00:23:15.662 --> 00:23:16.747
What?

00:23:16.747 --> 00:23:18.297
What's wrong?

00:23:19.147 --> 00:23:21.918
You haven't put your phone down all day.

00:23:21.918 --> 00:23:25.178
You had a blind date
and now you're hoping he calls back.

00:23:27.904 --> 00:23:31.593
If he still hasn't texted by now,
he's not interested.

00:23:31.593 --> 00:23:34.984
My husband and I met on a blind date.

00:23:34.984 --> 00:23:36.689
Is every guy the same way?

00:23:36.689 --> 00:23:38.145
Yes. Every single one.

00:23:38.145 --> 00:23:41.864
What if I introduce you
to a seriously great guy?

00:23:41.864 --> 00:23:43.440
He's a Y University grad,

00:23:43.440 --> 00:23:45.522
jumped right into his master's after college,

00:23:45.522 --> 00:23:47.522
and finished his PhD in the U.S.

00:23:47.522 --> 00:23:49.695
He works at S Electronics now,

00:23:49.695 --> 00:23:53.449
and they recruited him with an offer
over one hundred million won.

00:23:53.449 --> 00:23:54.464
One hundred million?

00:23:54.464 --> 00:23:57.578
That was three years back,
so he's probably earning more by now.

00:23:57.578 --> 00:23:59.564
Plus, he has zero interest in nightlife,

00:23:59.564 --> 00:24:03.125
and he's one of those rare guys
who pays no attention to other women.

00:24:03.125 --> 00:24:07.464
So why hasn't someone like that
found anyone yet?

00:24:10.215 --> 00:24:11.798
You know the nerdy type, right?

00:24:11.798 --> 00:24:13.594
He hit the books so hard

00:24:13.594 --> 00:24:15.898
that he's a little awkward socially?

00:24:15.898 --> 00:24:17.397
And looks-wise, he's sort of...

00:24:17.397 --> 00:24:18.605
Got it.

00:24:18.605 --> 00:24:20.317
So he's not much to look at either.

00:24:20.317 --> 00:24:22.258
Does a guy's appearance even matter to you?

00:24:22.258 --> 00:24:23.731
Yeah.

00:24:23.731 --> 00:24:25.480
It's not on purpose,

00:24:25.480 --> 00:24:27.198
but looks are all you see at first.

00:24:27.198 --> 00:24:29.597
That fades with time.

00:24:29.597 --> 00:24:30.986
Honestly,

00:24:30.986 --> 00:24:33.477
with your resume,
how would you ever meet a guy like that?

00:24:33.477 --> 00:24:35.605
We may look impressive on the surface,

00:24:35.605 --> 00:24:37.118
but there's not
a whole lot of substance behind it.

00:24:37.118 --> 00:24:38.677
Just go see him.

00:24:38.677 --> 00:24:40.670
I'll send him your number.

00:24:42.372 --> 00:24:44.605
Wait a second.

00:24:44.605 --> 00:24:48.511
Give me a bit more time
and I'll get back to you.

00:24:49.147 --> 00:24:52.001
Yeah, no problem.

00:24:52.001 --> 00:24:53.226
Let me know when you're ready.

00:24:53.226 --> 00:24:54.147
Oh, right.

00:24:54.147 --> 00:24:57.064
Is anyone coming to help us?

00:24:57.064 --> 00:25:00.815
I love this place,
but the staff here are so slacking.

00:25:03.272 --> 00:25:05.403
Excuse me.

00:25:16.522 --> 00:25:18.416
Thank you.

00:25:19.326 --> 00:25:20.352
Ui Yeong.

00:25:20.352 --> 00:25:22.771
Have I been waiting too long for a follow-up?

00:25:22.771 --> 00:25:24.672
I must be seeing things.

00:25:26.542 --> 00:25:29.522
How come you're here...

00:25:29.522 --> 00:25:32.271
Did you drink? Your face is flushed.

00:25:32.271 --> 00:25:36.218
I had a company dinner tonight, so...

00:25:36.218 --> 00:25:39.352
Were you on your way somewhere?

00:25:39.352 --> 00:25:41.014
Oh, I have a business trip,

00:25:41.014 --> 00:25:42.712
so I was on my way to the airport.

00:25:42.712 --> 00:25:44.423
Oh, is that so?

00:25:44.423 --> 00:25:46.324
Once I'm back...

00:25:46.324 --> 00:25:48.571
You know...

00:25:49.605 --> 00:25:52.109
Have you gone on any more blind dates?

00:25:52.109 --> 00:25:54.278
What?

00:25:54.278 --> 00:25:55.304
No,

00:25:55.304 --> 00:25:57.156
nothing's come my way either.

00:25:57.156 --> 00:25:59.043
Oh, okay.

00:25:59.043 --> 00:26:02.397
I actually got an offer though.

00:26:02.397 --> 00:26:05.672
So should I turn it down?

00:26:07.480 --> 00:26:09.258
Well...

00:26:10.714 --> 00:26:13.155
I don't see how that's my call.

00:26:13.155 --> 00:26:16.925
It's your decision to make.

00:26:16.925 --> 00:26:18.559
Yeah.

00:26:19.188 --> 00:26:21.604
Forget I brought it up.

00:26:22.234 --> 00:26:24.023
Get going.

00:26:24.023 --> 00:26:25.643
Hold on.

00:26:29.605 --> 00:26:31.254
I'll contact you after I'm back.

00:26:31.254 --> 00:26:32.949
Contact me?

00:26:39.772 --> 00:26:42.500
The stain really did come out.

00:26:48.647 --> 00:26:50.425
Nice.

00:26:55.078 --> 00:26:56.383
About the dress.

00:26:56.383 --> 00:27:00.476
I followed your advice
and the stain disappeared completely!

00:27:02.605 --> 00:27:03.931
Thanking him was just the excuse.

00:27:03.931 --> 00:27:06.978
What I really wanted was a second date.

00:27:06.978 --> 00:27:10.778
Bumping into him again
felt like a sign from above.

00:27:13.355 --> 00:27:15.199
He's bound to read my message, right?

00:27:16.276 --> 00:27:19.029
[111 hours since the blind date]

00:27:19.029 --> 00:27:20.872
[Song Tae Seop]

00:27:21.531 --> 00:27:23.220
[I followed your advice
and the stain disappeared completely!]

00:27:25.939 --> 00:27:28.796
Was that just small talk
and I read too much into it?

00:27:35.045 --> 00:27:36.064
- No way!
- It's gorgeous!

00:27:36.064 --> 00:27:38.448
It looks so upscale!

00:27:38.448 --> 00:27:40.480
Consider this payback for those amazing melons.

00:27:40.480 --> 00:27:42.304
Wait, so we can have some right now?

00:27:42.304 --> 00:27:42.898
Absolutely.

00:27:42.898 --> 00:27:44.572
Let's eat.

00:27:49.814 --> 00:27:51.569
That looks incredible.

00:28:01.988 --> 00:28:03.939
It's so sweet and so good.

00:28:03.939 --> 00:28:05.389
The quality of the ingredients was outstanding.

00:28:05.389 --> 00:28:07.731
Marketing can't wait to launch these,

00:28:07.731 --> 00:28:08.829
so make sure the purchase orders go through.

00:28:08.829 --> 00:28:10.379
Got it.

00:28:11.647 --> 00:28:13.669
This is incredible. Right?

00:28:13.669 --> 00:28:16.044
Yeah, it's incredible.

00:28:16.044 --> 00:28:17.522
But do you think people will buy it?

00:28:17.522 --> 00:28:21.390
130,000 won could make it
the priciest hotel shaved ice around.

00:28:22.105 --> 00:28:23.844
But considering what goes into it,

00:28:23.844 --> 00:28:25.689
the price isn't that unreasonable,

00:28:25.689 --> 00:28:28.243
and people are paying
for the date experience too.

00:28:28.243 --> 00:28:29.725
So let's back the chef and run with it.

00:28:29.725 --> 00:28:31.484
- Absolutely.
- Got it.

00:28:38.640 --> 00:28:39.861
I'm Lee Jeong Woo.

00:28:39.861 --> 00:28:41.701
Na Ri gave me your number.

00:28:41.701 --> 00:28:44.860
I'd love to meet up this Saturday.
Would that work for you?

00:28:44.860 --> 00:28:47.652
I told her I'd let her know
if I didn't get a follow-up,

00:28:47.652 --> 00:28:51.754
but by now, she probably knows it's a dead end.

00:28:57.731 --> 00:29:01.848
He couldn't even bother to read my text?
That's harsh.

00:29:05.480 --> 00:29:07.486
Saturday sounds good to me.

00:29:07.486 --> 00:29:09.299
What spot works for you?

00:29:13.812 --> 00:29:15.687
I'm done too, then.

00:29:15.687 --> 00:29:20.579
[6:00 p.m., Lee Jeong Woo,
Yangjae, CAFE CATTLE&TEA]

00:29:25.906 --> 00:29:27.915
[Melon tasting scorecard]

00:29:36.799 --> 00:29:39.594
Looks and personality are things
I have to consider.

00:29:41.171 --> 00:29:42.716
[Looks]

00:29:42.716 --> 00:29:45.016
[Personality]
Personality.

00:29:46.023 --> 00:29:48.056
Also...

00:29:48.056 --> 00:29:50.064
Someone who's happy to go on dates

00:29:50.064 --> 00:29:52.732
on their days off would be ideal.

00:29:54.474 --> 00:29:57.028
Then I guess stamina is a factor?

00:29:57.773 --> 00:29:59.773
A solid build would be a plus.

00:29:59.773 --> 00:30:02.491
[Physical Build]

00:30:03.110 --> 00:30:04.914
Also... money.

00:30:04.914 --> 00:30:06.406
Our spending habits should line up.

00:30:06.406 --> 00:30:06.960
Right.

00:30:06.960 --> 00:30:08.522
[Financial Stability]

00:30:08.522 --> 00:30:11.173
Someone who doesn't hold back spending
on dates would be nice.

00:30:11.173 --> 00:30:12.373
Humor...

00:30:12.373 --> 00:30:13.620
that's something you just can't do without.

00:30:13.620 --> 00:30:14.333
[Humor]

00:30:14.333 --> 00:30:16.397
T-types are a no-go for me.

00:30:16.397 --> 00:30:18.875
F only, period.

00:30:18.875 --> 00:30:20.212
[F for empathy!!]

00:30:20.212 --> 00:30:24.222
I'm not messing around
with this second blind date.

00:30:32.472 --> 00:30:34.249
That bag costs a fortune.

00:30:34.249 --> 00:30:35.190
Go with something else.

00:30:35.190 --> 00:30:37.272
Seriously...

00:30:37.272 --> 00:30:39.397
You told me people size me up

00:30:39.397 --> 00:30:41.982
based on what bag I'm carrying.

00:30:41.982 --> 00:30:43.670
You want your daughter to be looked down on?

00:30:43.670 --> 00:30:46.661
I also don't want people overestimating you.

00:31:16.933 --> 00:31:19.686
[190 hours since the blind date]

00:31:19.686 --> 00:31:21.273
[Second Blind Date Day]

00:31:21.273 --> 00:31:23.030
Perfect.

00:31:28.778 --> 00:31:31.545
Glad to hear it.
That dress looked perfect on you.

00:31:31.545 --> 00:31:33.046
Are you free this evening?

00:31:33.046 --> 00:31:35.876
Oh, now you text me?

00:31:37.469 --> 00:31:40.339
I'm on my way to a blind date right now.

00:31:42.272 --> 00:31:43.754
My reply was a bit late, wasn't it?

00:31:43.754 --> 00:31:45.881
The business trip had me swamped, so I...

00:31:45.881 --> 00:31:47.591
I already have plans.

00:31:47.591 --> 00:31:49.682
I'll reach out next time.

00:31:55.892 --> 00:31:58.149
I'll be waiting to hear from you.

00:32:38.198 --> 00:32:41.738
A cafe is where he chose for the blind date.

00:32:41.738 --> 00:32:46.438
If I'm not his type,
he can down a quick coffee and leave.

00:32:46.438 --> 00:32:50.638
No money or time wasted. Very practical of him.

00:32:50.638 --> 00:32:54.372
So that's what it takes
to pull in over a hundred million won a year?

00:33:25.895 --> 00:33:27.395
You know the nerdy type, right?

00:33:27.395 --> 00:33:29.149
He hit the books so hard

00:33:29.149 --> 00:33:31.651
that he's a little awkward socially?

00:33:31.651 --> 00:33:34.698
And looks-wise, he's sort of...

00:33:43.874 --> 00:33:46.209
Late? Then just say so, for God's sake.

00:33:46.209 --> 00:33:49.677
If his time matters, so does everyone else's.

00:33:51.260 --> 00:33:52.972
I'm late.

00:33:54.885 --> 00:33:56.934
Did I say that too late?

00:34:08.753 --> 00:34:11.026
Are you Lee Jeong Woo by any chance?

00:34:11.026 --> 00:34:13.626
Yes, I'm Jeong Woo.

00:34:13.626 --> 00:34:15.536
You're Ui Yeong, right?

00:34:17.897 --> 00:34:19.582
Yes.

00:34:30.355 --> 00:34:34.430
So much for "don't get your hopes up."

00:34:35.981 --> 00:34:39.977
Ui Yeong, quit smiling like this.

00:34:42.188 --> 00:34:44.064
[Looks]

00:34:49.266 --> 00:34:52.030
You look like a movie star.

00:34:53.105 --> 00:34:54.906
Nobody's ever told me that before.

00:34:54.906 --> 00:34:55.847
Is that so?

00:34:55.847 --> 00:34:58.266
So, are you into movies at all?

00:34:58.266 --> 00:35:00.657
Who doesn't enjoy a good movie?

00:35:00.657 --> 00:35:02.064
Exactly.

00:35:02.064 --> 00:35:03.346
Fair point.

00:35:03.346 --> 00:35:05.466
What kind of movies are you into?

00:35:05.466 --> 00:35:09.026
Comedies and rom-coms are my thing.

00:35:09.026 --> 00:35:11.564
Those two are the only ones I skip.

00:35:11.564 --> 00:35:12.786
What?

00:35:12.786 --> 00:35:16.722
Is he disagreeing just to spite me?

00:35:18.299 --> 00:35:20.890
[Zero humor, zero empathy]

00:35:20.890 --> 00:35:24.855
Our tastes couldn't be more different.

00:35:28.772 --> 00:35:31.982
I heard from Na Ri you're at S Electronics.

00:35:31.982 --> 00:35:34.698
The bonuses there are massive, aren't they?

00:35:35.439 --> 00:35:38.947
Plus, the perks are supposedly amazing.

00:35:38.947 --> 00:35:42.081
That kind of package would fire me up.

00:35:45.439 --> 00:35:48.212
It's no different from any other desk job.

00:35:49.689 --> 00:35:51.460
On a blind date,

00:35:51.460 --> 00:35:54.510
I don't care how much the other person makes.

00:35:57.023 --> 00:35:58.480
Hold on,

00:35:58.480 --> 00:36:01.217
did he just call me out?

00:36:01.217 --> 00:36:03.426
[Personality, fail]

00:36:18.026 --> 00:36:19.488
Ui Yeong.

00:36:19.488 --> 00:36:21.704
Stick it out till the very end today.

00:36:40.911 --> 00:36:44.893
What's the story behind your neck tattoo?

00:36:47.314 --> 00:36:50.060
S Electronics is known for being rigid,

00:36:50.060 --> 00:36:52.631
yet you come off as pretty laid-back.

00:36:52.631 --> 00:36:56.322
You're not some exec's kid
in disguise, are you?

00:36:58.272 --> 00:37:00.026
Wouldn't that be nice?

00:37:00.026 --> 00:37:00.811
Sorry, what?

00:37:00.811 --> 00:37:03.454
If that were true, why would I be here?

00:37:05.323 --> 00:37:08.731
All you've talked about is my job and money.

00:37:08.731 --> 00:37:11.439
I know my resume is why you showed up,

00:37:11.439 --> 00:37:14.006
but being that blatant is a real turnoff.

00:37:15.017 --> 00:37:17.564
I blow through every cent I make,

00:37:17.564 --> 00:37:20.680
so even if we end up together,

00:37:20.680 --> 00:37:23.877
don't count on me footing the bills.

00:37:23.877 --> 00:37:25.971
What an absolute ass.

00:37:25.971 --> 00:37:29.104
Someone obviously forced him to show up.

00:37:30.480 --> 00:37:31.647
Listen,

00:37:31.647 --> 00:37:34.797
I see you like being straightforward,

00:37:34.797 --> 00:37:39.365
but I'm not looking to rely on a man's wallet.

00:37:40.075 --> 00:37:41.635
I've got the check today.

00:37:41.635 --> 00:37:43.410
Let's wrap up and head out.

00:37:47.865 --> 00:37:48.910
Sure,

00:37:48.910 --> 00:37:51.585
then, over here, please.

00:37:54.564 --> 00:37:56.749
Two macarons and a tiramisu cake,

00:37:56.749 --> 00:38:00.135
plus an iced mocha loaded with whipped cream.

00:38:01.615 --> 00:38:03.680
Anything for you?

00:38:04.468 --> 00:38:06.225
Just that, please.

00:38:22.397 --> 00:38:26.362
The world is full of total lunatics.

00:38:26.362 --> 00:38:27.670
I just

00:38:27.670 --> 00:38:29.790
really love sweets.

00:38:30.950 --> 00:38:33.669
You're really done now, right?

00:38:39.647 --> 00:38:41.355
Why is Tae Seop here of all places?

00:38:41.355 --> 00:38:42.970
What's wrong?

00:38:43.814 --> 00:38:45.681
I get dizzy when I stand up too fast.

00:38:57.856 --> 00:38:59.862
Who's that man over there?

00:39:01.355 --> 00:39:02.522
A former boyfriend?

00:39:02.522 --> 00:39:04.009
The one before him?

00:39:04.009 --> 00:39:06.869
- So the ex before that ex.
- Oh, just shut up.

00:39:07.814 --> 00:39:09.950
Why would you swear at...

00:39:09.950 --> 00:39:12.119
You clearly don't care about me anyway.

00:39:12.119 --> 00:39:15.419
I'm heading out,
so let's say our goodbyes there.

00:39:19.814 --> 00:39:22.009
How do you plan to reach the exit?

00:39:26.731 --> 00:39:28.176
Wait, your dress got caught...

00:39:28.176 --> 00:39:29.303
Please hold still...

00:39:29.303 --> 00:39:31.106
Just a second...

00:39:32.397 --> 00:39:34.813
Get your hands off me.

00:39:38.740 --> 00:39:40.731
Ui Yeong?

00:39:40.731 --> 00:39:42.605
Oh, Tae Seop.

00:39:42.605 --> 00:39:43.897
Are you okay? Do you know this person?

00:39:43.897 --> 00:39:45.407
What?

00:39:48.030 --> 00:39:49.703
Yeah, she does.

00:39:52.031 --> 00:39:53.800
I'm her brother.

00:39:53.800 --> 00:39:55.188
Brother?

00:39:55.188 --> 00:39:56.872
My bad, sis.

00:39:56.872 --> 00:39:59.747
I shouldn't have opened your piggy bank.

00:39:59.747 --> 00:40:01.701
I had no clue
you'd saved it since grade school.

00:40:01.701 --> 00:40:05.093
I thought you said you had no siblings.

00:40:06.397 --> 00:40:08.187
She's technically an only child.

00:40:08.187 --> 00:40:09.887
I'm just her cousin.

00:40:09.887 --> 00:40:12.346
But what about you?

00:40:12.346 --> 00:40:15.395
Since when do you know my sister so well?

00:40:20.731 --> 00:40:25.113
This isn't what it looks like.

00:40:26.107 --> 00:40:28.687
Oh, I see.

00:40:28.687 --> 00:40:30.856
The noise caught me off guard.

00:40:30.856 --> 00:40:32.588
Sorry about that.

00:40:32.588 --> 00:40:35.856
Sorry for the scene.

00:40:35.856 --> 00:40:37.829
I should get going.

00:40:37.829 --> 00:40:39.647
I'll reach out later.

00:40:39.647 --> 00:40:41.213
Okay.

00:41:02.676 --> 00:41:04.316
Cousins?

00:41:04.316 --> 00:41:06.572
He definitely didn't fall for that.

00:41:07.522 --> 00:41:09.277
Before you misunderstand,

00:41:09.277 --> 00:41:11.397
your skirt had slipped up,

00:41:11.397 --> 00:41:12.814
so I was fixing it for you.

00:41:12.814 --> 00:41:15.355
If he hadn't loaded up on coffee and cake...

00:41:15.355 --> 00:41:18.397
Either way, sorry I grabbed you like that.

00:41:18.397 --> 00:41:20.168
I was flustered.

00:41:20.814 --> 00:41:22.056
You hear me?

00:41:22.056 --> 00:41:23.630
Yeah.

00:41:25.272 --> 00:41:26.297
It's okay.

00:41:26.297 --> 00:41:29.596
The act wasn't very convincing,
but I appreciate you trying.

00:41:29.596 --> 00:41:31.117
Anyway, take care.

00:41:31.117 --> 00:41:33.058
So the blind date is done?

00:41:33.058 --> 00:41:34.814
Yes, it's done.

00:41:34.814 --> 00:41:35.458
You can leave now.

00:41:35.458 --> 00:41:36.805
You called it off first

00:41:36.805 --> 00:41:38.939
because I'm not your type.

00:41:38.939 --> 00:41:40.638
- Am I wrong?
- Exactly.

00:41:40.638 --> 00:41:43.567
So please just go already.

00:41:47.772 --> 00:41:49.455
Hey.

00:41:52.647 --> 00:41:55.120
If you're free right now,

00:41:55.897 --> 00:41:57.831
how about a drink?

00:42:07.847 --> 00:42:10.052
Nothing to do with the blind date.

00:42:11.939 --> 00:42:14.428
Excuse me, two draft beers, please.

00:42:14.428 --> 00:42:15.247
Sure.

00:42:15.247 --> 00:42:17.228
Then you're covering this.

00:42:17.228 --> 00:42:19.814
I got the cafe, so the drinks are yours.

00:42:19.814 --> 00:42:21.355
Fine.

00:42:23.227 --> 00:42:27.903
Blind dates usually involve a meal.

00:42:29.023 --> 00:42:32.491
That's why I hadn't eaten all day.

00:42:42.887 --> 00:42:45.023
What are you, a hamster?

00:42:45.023 --> 00:42:47.214
Take it easy.

00:42:48.731 --> 00:42:50.467
Not having any?

00:42:51.814 --> 00:42:54.846
No. That cake left a sweet taste I can't shake.

00:43:18.023 --> 00:43:19.822
Seriously?

00:43:19.822 --> 00:43:21.868
Why are you chugging like that?

00:43:21.868 --> 00:43:24.376
Don't come at me for how I drink.

00:43:24.981 --> 00:43:26.621
By the way,

00:43:26.621 --> 00:43:28.772
I'm older,

00:43:28.772 --> 00:43:30.477
so mind if I talk casually?

00:43:30.477 --> 00:43:32.355
Too late for that.

00:43:32.355 --> 00:43:34.261
Then I will too.

00:43:47.856 --> 00:43:50.110
That's got to be a blind date.

00:43:52.314 --> 00:43:54.781
Maybe I should've talked her out of it...

00:43:55.524 --> 00:43:57.522
[Had plans already] [A cousin...?]
[A sibling...?]

00:43:57.522 --> 00:44:00.446
Excuse me, we close in ten minutes.

00:44:00.446 --> 00:44:02.198
Right,

00:44:02.198 --> 00:44:04.541
let me wrap up and leave. My apologies.

00:44:09.397 --> 00:44:12.355
My plan is simple.

00:44:12.355 --> 00:44:16.056
I want to find the right person
before time runs out

00:44:16.056 --> 00:44:18.680
and build a good life together.

00:44:20.265 --> 00:44:21.814
By the way,

00:44:21.814 --> 00:44:24.023
what I can't figure out is you.

00:44:24.023 --> 00:44:26.438
Why did you even show up today?

00:44:30.772 --> 00:44:32.694
Same as yours.

00:44:33.813 --> 00:44:35.865
To meet someone great.

00:44:35.865 --> 00:44:37.005
What?

00:44:37.005 --> 00:44:39.480
Josu Saman Ko?

00:44:39.480 --> 00:44:41.153
No,

00:44:41.153 --> 00:44:43.951
I was saying, meeting someone great...

00:45:04.093 --> 00:45:05.678
That was almost a fender bender.

00:45:05.678 --> 00:45:09.731
That's the whole point of blind dates.

00:45:12.852 --> 00:45:16.149
Fine, I get that...
so why wasn't I good enough?

00:45:16.804 --> 00:45:18.198
What?

00:45:18.816 --> 00:45:21.897
I'm not looking for a fight,
just an honest answer.

00:45:21.897 --> 00:45:25.803
Sure, I don't earn what you do,

00:45:25.803 --> 00:45:28.147
but my income is stable.

00:45:28.147 --> 00:45:32.147
My mom is still working, and my dad,

00:45:32.147 --> 00:45:34.716
even though we live apart,
still has a job at a public company.

00:45:34.716 --> 00:45:38.964
As for personality,
I've been called too nice, maybe,

00:45:38.964 --> 00:45:41.800
but never unkind.

00:45:41.800 --> 00:45:44.605
When you look at the full picture,

00:45:44.605 --> 00:45:46.105
I'd say

00:45:46.105 --> 00:45:48.019
I'm a solid catch, wouldn't you?

00:45:51.272 --> 00:45:53.689
You're decent.

00:45:53.689 --> 00:45:56.444
You come off a bit like a people-pleaser,

00:45:57.395 --> 00:45:59.614
but I'd take that over someone cruel.

00:46:00.897 --> 00:46:02.140
So

00:46:02.140 --> 00:46:05.814
is it my appearance? I'm not attractive to you?

00:46:05.814 --> 00:46:07.956
You're

00:46:09.522 --> 00:46:11.251
good-looking.

00:46:13.522 --> 00:46:16.867
This makes no sense.

00:46:16.867 --> 00:46:17.897
Hey.

00:46:17.897 --> 00:46:20.047
Just tell me straight

00:46:20.047 --> 00:46:22.980
so I can improve for the next one.

00:46:22.980 --> 00:46:25.098
Down that glass and I'll explain.

00:46:26.522 --> 00:46:28.853
I was already planning to.

00:46:28.853 --> 00:46:31.433
Once I finish this, I'll forget tonight

00:46:31.433 --> 00:46:33.693
and go find someone truly worth it.

00:46:33.693 --> 00:46:35.400
You'll see.

00:46:40.522 --> 00:46:41.939
Actually,

00:46:41.939 --> 00:46:45.113
could you introduce me to someone?

00:46:45.113 --> 00:46:47.854
Got any friends as good-looking as you?

00:46:47.854 --> 00:46:49.013
Seriously?

00:46:49.013 --> 00:46:52.535
You're asking that to the person
you just had a blind date with?

00:46:52.535 --> 00:46:54.313
Besides, I don't have friends to introduce.

00:46:54.313 --> 00:46:56.213
Try someone else.

00:46:58.251 --> 00:47:00.300
You're so boring.

00:47:07.897 --> 00:47:10.310
Where did the time go?

00:47:16.188 --> 00:47:18.530
You really put that food away.

00:47:18.530 --> 00:47:20.695
Thanks for the treat.

00:47:21.490 --> 00:47:24.240
Now that you're full, how about a walk?

00:47:25.772 --> 00:47:27.661
I ate too much.

00:47:39.899 --> 00:47:42.676
Hey, follow me over here.

00:47:50.564 --> 00:47:52.394
Come on, follow me.

00:48:01.767 --> 00:48:03.238
What?

00:48:07.064 --> 00:48:09.077
I worried over nothing.

00:48:10.939 --> 00:48:12.664
Over here.

00:48:19.939 --> 00:48:21.314
Do you know what this is?

00:48:21.314 --> 00:48:24.007
It's a merry-go-round.

00:48:24.007 --> 00:48:27.048
I ruled the playground as a kid.

00:48:27.048 --> 00:48:28.300
No,

00:48:28.300 --> 00:48:29.947
the official name.

00:48:29.947 --> 00:48:32.350
Wait, it has a different name?

00:48:33.643 --> 00:48:34.978
Yeah.

00:48:35.943 --> 00:48:37.605
A spinning stage.

00:48:38.439 --> 00:48:40.233
A spinning stage?

00:48:52.779 --> 00:48:54.964
- Shall I spin it?
- Yeah.

00:49:02.818 --> 00:49:04.945
This feels great.

00:49:12.945 --> 00:49:15.436
Hold on tight.

00:49:27.795 --> 00:49:29.566
Hold on!

00:49:29.566 --> 00:49:31.860
Stop it.

00:49:31.860 --> 00:49:35.242
I'm about to throw up, quit it!

00:49:36.793 --> 00:49:37.825
Hey.

00:49:37.825 --> 00:49:39.064
You alright?

00:49:39.064 --> 00:49:40.627
Hey...

00:49:44.689 --> 00:49:46.670
Are you going to puke?

00:49:46.670 --> 00:49:49.075
Want me to pat your back?

00:49:49.075 --> 00:49:50.462
Everything's spinning.

00:49:50.462 --> 00:49:52.225
Are you fine?

00:49:54.355 --> 00:49:56.449
It's still spinning.

00:49:56.449 --> 00:49:57.709
Look at that,

00:49:57.709 --> 00:49:59.896
the whole world is spinning.

00:50:26.689 --> 00:50:30.051
You're seriously hilarious.

00:50:31.272 --> 00:50:32.846
You know that?

00:50:38.347 --> 00:50:40.186
Right back at you.

00:51:04.623 --> 00:51:06.754
This is trouble.

00:51:13.939 --> 00:51:15.972
My heart is fluttering.

00:51:16.840 --> 00:51:19.346
My mind keeps wandering.

00:51:20.814 --> 00:51:22.689
What if

00:51:22.689 --> 00:51:26.733
I just trusted him completely?

00:51:28.313 --> 00:51:30.361
It might turn out better

00:51:32.272 --> 00:51:34.449
than I think.

00:51:37.023 --> 00:51:38.995
But...

00:51:39.616 --> 00:51:42.415
I'm not sleeping with you.

00:51:43.133 --> 00:51:44.667
Why?

00:51:45.856 --> 00:51:48.000
Isn't this

00:51:48.000 --> 00:51:49.714
nice?

00:51:52.064 --> 00:51:53.635
Yes.

00:51:55.148 --> 00:51:58.014
I love it. That's the problem.

00:52:02.522 --> 00:52:04.268
Ui Yeong!

00:52:05.856 --> 00:52:08.230
Since she was the one who arranged this,

00:52:08.230 --> 00:52:11.398
I couldn't act on my feelings.

00:52:11.398 --> 00:52:14.280
If Na Ri ever learned the truth,

00:52:15.023 --> 00:52:17.508
that alone would be a nightmare.

00:52:17.508 --> 00:52:18.729
What took you so long?

00:52:18.729 --> 00:52:20.480
I've been waiting on pins and needles!

00:52:20.480 --> 00:52:22.163
So how was it?

00:52:27.605 --> 00:52:29.921
Wait, did something happen?

00:52:30.581 --> 00:52:31.846
You look like you have a story.

00:52:31.846 --> 00:52:33.883
I knew it!

00:52:35.064 --> 00:52:37.428
Tell me everything.

00:52:38.105 --> 00:52:39.565
It went really well.

00:52:39.565 --> 00:52:42.605
Jeong Woo was exactly my type.

00:52:42.605 --> 00:52:44.852
For real? Even his looks?

00:52:47.480 --> 00:52:50.064
Yeah, he was a bit stiff at first,

00:52:50.064 --> 00:52:53.406
but once he relaxed,
that shift was really appealing.

00:52:53.406 --> 00:52:54.866
We even went somewhere after

00:52:54.866 --> 00:52:56.814
and split four bottles of soju.

00:52:56.814 --> 00:52:57.945
No way!

00:52:57.945 --> 00:53:00.034
And then?

00:53:05.605 --> 00:53:07.500
Nothing else.

00:53:08.188 --> 00:53:09.355
That's all?

00:53:09.355 --> 00:53:10.412
That's all.

00:53:10.412 --> 00:53:12.964
Seriously, nothing?

00:53:14.939 --> 00:53:17.502
Four bottles of soju on a first date
and that's all?

00:53:17.502 --> 00:53:20.040
Did you at least dress up a little?

00:53:20.040 --> 00:53:22.682
People appreciate it when you make an effort.

00:53:34.520 --> 00:53:37.317
And that was my second blind date.

00:53:37.317 --> 00:53:41.409
He never even checked if I got home okay.

00:54:06.604 --> 00:54:08.725
Shin Ji Su, how did the blind date go?

00:54:08.725 --> 00:54:11.648
Actually, forget it.
It probably flopped, right?

00:54:31.577 --> 00:54:34.750
Back at the cafe, when your head was clear,

00:54:34.750 --> 00:54:37.882
you showed zero interest.

00:54:38.814 --> 00:54:43.346
At the bar, you just danced around the topic.

00:54:43.950 --> 00:54:47.350
And now you're asking if this feels good?

00:54:50.095 --> 00:54:52.851
- Well, that's...
- Are you really into me?

00:54:52.851 --> 00:54:54.645
I don't think so.

00:54:54.645 --> 00:54:57.910
You're just caught up in tonight.

00:54:57.910 --> 00:54:59.370
Hey.

00:54:59.370 --> 00:55:01.989
You know what that's called?

00:55:02.689 --> 00:55:04.705
Lust.

00:55:04.705 --> 00:55:06.446
Hold on, you...

00:55:06.446 --> 00:55:08.037
Let's go.

00:55:09.147 --> 00:55:11.999
A blind date should feel light,

00:55:12.897 --> 00:55:15.378
but I overdid it with the drinks tonight.

00:55:18.897 --> 00:55:21.342
Find someone you genuinely care about.

00:55:27.772 --> 00:55:30.727
Someone worth every ounce of your heart.

00:55:31.605 --> 00:55:33.896
I hope that person comes along.

00:55:41.290 --> 00:55:43.605
Hey Jeong Woo, sorry to bother you,

00:55:43.605 --> 00:55:47.785
but can I get Lee Ui Yeong's number?

00:56:07.147 --> 00:56:09.673
I met the matchmaker at a social event.

00:56:09.673 --> 00:56:12.206
She kept probing to figure me out.

00:56:12.206 --> 00:56:14.033
I wasn't ready to come out,

00:56:14.033 --> 00:56:15.673
but you helped me avoid it.

00:56:15.673 --> 00:56:17.398
Consider this thanks.

00:56:34.397 --> 00:56:37.210
Melon bingsu with a line out the door?

00:56:39.373 --> 00:56:43.883
MIMI posted about our hotel's bingsu online.

00:56:44.981 --> 00:56:47.939
Is MIMI famous or something?

00:56:47.939 --> 00:56:49.731
Wait,

00:56:49.731 --> 00:56:51.939
you've never heard of MIMI?
She's in Oh My Girl.

00:56:51.939 --> 00:56:54.064
It's a girl group. She does variety shows too.

00:56:54.064 --> 00:56:55.574
She's incredibly popular and adorable.

00:56:55.574 --> 00:56:56.634
I know.

00:56:56.634 --> 00:56:59.314
Oh my God...

00:56:59.314 --> 00:57:02.188
- My gosh.
- Gosh.

00:57:02.188 --> 00:57:03.061
Gosh.

00:57:03.061 --> 00:57:04.853
Is it possible to change the melon order?

00:57:04.853 --> 00:57:05.673
Absolutely.

00:57:05.673 --> 00:57:07.899
I already confirmed
with the supplier before we started.

00:57:07.899 --> 00:57:09.713
Media outlets are reaching out as well.

00:57:09.713 --> 00:57:12.571
We'll offer a room-and-bingsu package,

00:57:12.571 --> 00:57:15.031
so factor that in
and lock down as much supply as you can.

00:57:15.031 --> 00:57:15.712
Got it.

00:57:15.712 --> 00:57:20.943
Celebrity power is no joke, right?

00:57:21.814 --> 00:57:25.125
She wouldn't have posted about it
if the bingsu wasn't that good.

00:57:25.125 --> 00:57:28.882
Someone put in the effort to develop the recipe
and find quality melons.

00:57:28.882 --> 00:57:30.994
- Let's recognize the people who earned it.
- Yeah...

00:57:30.994 --> 00:57:31.923
Right.

00:57:31.923 --> 00:57:33.592
That's exactly my point.

00:57:33.592 --> 00:57:35.136
Ui Yeong, well done.

00:57:35.136 --> 00:57:36.656
Seriously, well done.

00:57:36.656 --> 00:57:37.836
Same to you, Chef.

00:57:37.836 --> 00:57:40.362
- Oh yes, Chef, wonderful work.
- You're the best.

00:57:40.362 --> 00:57:42.835
You too.

00:57:44.982 --> 00:57:48.156
[Conference Room]
- Great job. - Good job, everyone.

00:57:49.522 --> 00:57:52.735
Do you have any plans after work tonight?

00:57:52.735 --> 00:57:55.162
Nothing on my schedule.

00:58:06.397 --> 00:58:08.147
Any second now...

00:58:08.147 --> 00:58:09.927
there she is.

00:58:10.672 --> 00:58:12.589
Have a seat here.

00:58:12.589 --> 00:58:13.614
No trouble getting here?

00:58:13.614 --> 00:58:14.758
What can I get you?

00:58:14.758 --> 00:58:17.055
- A beer for me, please.
- Okay.

00:58:17.719 --> 00:58:19.630
- Glad you could make it.
- So glad you're here.

00:58:19.630 --> 00:58:22.211
Three people from the Purchasing Team
and the general manager?

00:58:22.211 --> 00:58:23.731
That's a unique combo.

00:58:23.731 --> 00:58:26.591
We actually have a small group at work.

00:58:26.591 --> 00:58:27.771
It's called the Eat Eat Club.

00:58:27.771 --> 00:58:28.897
Pardon?

00:58:28.897 --> 00:58:30.235
No, Eat, Eat, Club.

00:58:30.235 --> 00:58:32.810
We explore restaurants
and try new dishes together.

00:58:32.810 --> 00:58:36.064
She claims it was for professional development,

00:58:36.064 --> 00:58:38.439
but really it's just a group

00:58:38.439 --> 00:58:41.802
that eats well and blows off steam.

00:58:41.802 --> 00:58:42.856
Tonight is different though.

00:58:42.856 --> 00:58:45.523
We're here to celebrate the bingsu success.

00:58:45.523 --> 00:58:48.175
Everything is my treat.

00:58:50.814 --> 00:58:51.923
It's hot.

00:58:51.923 --> 00:58:53.342
- It's hot.
- Thank you.

00:58:53.342 --> 00:58:54.439
Thank you.

00:58:54.439 --> 00:58:56.188
Looks delicious.

00:58:56.188 --> 00:58:58.959
- That outfit today is...
- Pretty?

00:58:59.970 --> 00:59:01.221
Okay, fresh gloves on.

00:59:01.221 --> 00:59:02.940
This looks amazing.

00:59:02.940 --> 00:59:05.632
Oh wait,
have you never tried chicken feet before?

00:59:05.632 --> 00:59:06.731
Never.

00:59:06.731 --> 00:59:09.229
That's right, you grew up overseas.

00:59:09.229 --> 00:59:11.148
Here's what you should know about chicken feet.

00:59:11.148 --> 00:59:14.230
There's nothing better for relieving stress.

00:59:14.230 --> 00:59:15.856
Give it a try.

00:59:15.856 --> 00:59:18.115
- Really?
- Yeah.

00:59:18.115 --> 00:59:19.117
Okay.

00:59:19.117 --> 00:59:21.192
- Since you're in Korea, you should try it.
- Give it a try.

00:59:21.192 --> 00:59:22.147
High five!

00:59:22.147 --> 00:59:23.952
- High five!
- High five!

00:59:23.952 --> 00:59:26.617
Four chicken feet, high four, high four!

00:59:34.254 --> 00:59:35.926
What do you think?

00:59:39.174 --> 00:59:41.602
- It's actually really good.
- Right?

00:59:43.314 --> 00:59:44.856
- Spicy?
- It's spicy, right?

00:59:44.856 --> 00:59:45.814
If it's too spicy, have some of this.

00:59:45.814 --> 00:59:48.194
I see why this helps with stress now.

00:59:48.194 --> 00:59:49.814
Right?

00:59:49.814 --> 00:59:51.230
But

00:59:51.230 --> 00:59:53.633
do you all get stressed out a lot?

00:59:53.633 --> 00:59:55.254
Your team always looks so upbeat.
I never would have guessed.

00:59:55.254 --> 00:59:56.981
Absolutely.

00:59:56.981 --> 01:00:01.114
I'm running on frustration all year round.

01:00:01.114 --> 01:00:04.075
In my case, the path
to a permanent position looks bleak.

01:00:04.075 --> 01:00:07.147
As for me, my blind date was a total wreck.

01:00:07.147 --> 01:00:08.814
Stay strong, Ui Yeong.

01:00:08.814 --> 01:00:09.894
Thanks.

01:00:09.894 --> 01:00:11.315
No complaints on my end.

01:00:11.315 --> 01:00:15.434
Sharing good food with all of you
is enough for me.

01:00:15.434 --> 01:00:16.254
All right.

01:00:16.254 --> 01:00:18.515
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

01:00:18.515 --> 01:00:20.469
Bottoms up!

01:00:25.147 --> 01:00:28.439
What took you so long?

01:00:28.439 --> 01:00:31.219
I planned to stop eating at seven.

01:00:31.219 --> 01:00:32.240
My bad,

01:00:32.240 --> 01:00:34.484
the roads were awful.

01:00:34.484 --> 01:00:35.859
But Sua,

01:00:35.859 --> 01:00:37.600
doesn't every diet begin tomorrow?

01:00:37.600 --> 01:00:38.799
Sua, listen.

01:00:38.799 --> 01:00:40.946
He wasn't feeling well
and even went to the hospital.

01:00:40.946 --> 01:00:41.660
Really?

01:00:41.660 --> 01:00:43.355
So no nagging today.

01:00:43.355 --> 01:00:44.959
No nagging.

01:00:44.959 --> 01:00:47.230
Where does it hurt? Is it really bad?

01:00:47.230 --> 01:00:48.647
Yeah, it hurts so much.

01:00:48.647 --> 01:00:50.772
I'm dying,

01:00:50.772 --> 01:00:52.620
I'm dying.

01:00:52.620 --> 01:00:54.120
You can't die.

01:00:54.120 --> 01:00:57.355
I know I can't, but I'm already dead.

01:00:57.355 --> 01:00:59.930
Could you just keep her for a month or so?

01:01:00.700 --> 01:01:02.981
The food was wonderful.

01:01:02.981 --> 01:01:04.853
You're cute.

01:01:10.064 --> 01:01:11.640
Chef,

01:01:11.640 --> 01:01:13.731
do you think

01:01:13.731 --> 01:01:17.110
I'll find the right melon for me someday too?

01:01:17.110 --> 01:01:21.406
You're talking
about a man right now, aren't you?

01:01:21.406 --> 01:01:22.720
Yes.

01:01:22.720 --> 01:01:25.880
Just two blind dates so far, right?

01:01:25.880 --> 01:01:28.078
What exactly are you looking for in someone?

01:01:30.897 --> 01:01:32.998
When I accidentally discovered

01:01:32.998 --> 01:01:36.956
my date's car was a luxury model,

01:01:36.956 --> 01:01:39.762
my pulse went up.

01:01:41.385 --> 01:01:43.265
But...

01:01:45.147 --> 01:01:47.023
I honestly couldn't

01:01:47.023 --> 01:01:51.280
pick it out if I saw it again.

01:01:51.280 --> 01:01:55.148
I can't even distinguish a sedan from an SUV.

01:01:55.148 --> 01:01:57.905
My license has been sitting
in a drawer for years.

01:02:09.939 --> 01:02:12.059
A pricey car

01:02:12.059 --> 01:02:14.880
or a huge salary...

01:02:19.897 --> 01:02:22.221
Here's the wine you ordered.

01:02:23.772 --> 01:02:27.147
Would you mind telling us about this wine?

01:02:27.147 --> 01:02:28.579
Of course.

01:02:28.579 --> 01:02:31.222
This is an everyday red
from Italy's Abruzzo region,

01:02:31.222 --> 01:02:32.397
with ripe fruit notes

01:02:32.397 --> 01:02:35.901
- and a bright acidity.
- Even if someone has stunning looks,

01:02:41.173 --> 01:02:46.036
impressive qualities on paper
don't guarantee a real connection.

01:03:04.864 --> 01:03:06.314
The key is

01:03:06.314 --> 01:03:09.186
being on the same wavelength.

01:03:09.186 --> 01:03:12.278
It takes two, not just one.

01:03:12.278 --> 01:03:14.853
So blind dates are fun.

01:03:14.853 --> 01:03:17.026
- Hello.
- Welcome.

01:03:23.441 --> 01:03:24.547
Give this a try.

01:03:24.547 --> 01:03:27.006
I think it'd look great on you.

01:03:27.006 --> 01:03:29.246
Sure, I'll try it on.

01:03:34.772 --> 01:03:37.213
Oh, that's stunning on you.

01:03:39.291 --> 01:03:41.543
I think a cute style would suit you, too.

01:03:41.543 --> 01:03:43.469
What about this one?

01:03:44.856 --> 01:03:47.232
Got anything darker?

01:03:47.232 --> 01:03:49.689
Preferably something that hides spills?

01:03:49.689 --> 01:03:51.518
Just a second.

01:03:53.605 --> 01:03:55.940
What do you think of this?

01:03:57.731 --> 01:03:59.693
Let me just take a quick look.

01:04:01.981 --> 01:04:03.981
Since I'm doing this,

01:04:03.981 --> 01:04:06.211
I'm going all in.

01:04:06.211 --> 01:04:08.661
- I'll try it on.
- Sure.

01:04:12.265 --> 01:04:17.419
So if you know anyone decent, please set me up.

01:04:18.188 --> 01:04:20.005
[New message]

01:04:28.272 --> 01:04:30.126
Look what I picked out for you.

01:04:30.126 --> 01:04:31.245
Isn't it beautiful?

01:04:31.245 --> 01:04:33.227
Sure, I'll take it.

01:04:36.055 --> 01:04:38.065
[You have a new message]

01:04:39.544 --> 01:04:41.561
Hi, nice to meet you.

01:04:41.561 --> 01:04:42.353
Hello.

01:04:42.353 --> 01:04:45.064
I'm Lee Ho Kwang. I sing and act on stage.

01:04:45.064 --> 01:04:46.399
Hi, I'm Yook Jun Seo.

01:04:46.399 --> 01:04:47.654
Are you free next Friday?

01:04:47.654 --> 01:04:48.816
You're Lee Ui Yeong, right?

01:04:48.816 --> 01:04:50.397
Nice to meet you.

01:04:50.397 --> 01:04:52.830
Would you like to grab a cup of coffee with me?

01:05:00.272 --> 01:05:02.089
Are you okay?

01:05:04.147 --> 01:05:06.269
Hi, nice to meet you.

01:05:07.064 --> 01:05:09.763
Hi, I got your number for a blind date.

01:05:10.522 --> 01:05:14.560
Every single one of these
is a blind date request?

01:05:25.855 --> 01:05:29.491
[How fast can you fall? Five seconds!]

01:05:36.491 --> 01:05:39.668
[Is it a green light?]

01:05:42.497 --> 01:05:46.050
[Looks]

01:05:48.753 --> 01:05:51.764
[Trust myself to him?]

01:05:53.814 --> 01:05:55.722
Even though it began as a tipsy rant...

01:05:55.722 --> 01:05:59.063
Hi, nice to meet you. You know who I am, right?

01:06:00.522 --> 01:06:03.480
Is there someone
going on blind dates before work?

01:06:03.480 --> 01:06:04.647
Yes, that's me.

01:06:04.647 --> 01:06:07.105
If I see her just one more time,
I'll know for sure.

01:06:07.105 --> 01:06:08.564
Why don't you try running into her...

01:06:08.564 --> 01:06:10.105
Oh, Ui Yeong.

01:06:10.105 --> 01:06:11.731
Why are you holding my hand?

01:06:11.731 --> 01:06:13.869
Is there a reason?

01:06:14.814 --> 01:06:16.825
I don't want to be completely fake with you.

01:06:16.825 --> 01:06:19.409
- None of those men
- Oh no.

01:06:19.409 --> 01:06:22.204
- turned out to be my type.
- Tae Seop.

01:06:22.204 --> 01:06:24.463
Did you come here to see me?